Garden Farms first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Garden Farms had a population of 449. The population density was {{convert|410.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Garden Farms was 381 (84.9%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 8 (1.8%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 20 (4.5%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 39 (8.7%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 58 persons (12.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Garden Farms CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0628210 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 174 households, out of which 49 (28.2%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 81 (46.6%) were married-couple households, 10 (5.7%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 54 (31.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 29 (16.7%) had a male householder with no partner present. 58 households (33.3%) were one person, and 18 (10.3%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.58.<ref name=DP1/> There were 105 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (60.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Garden Farms CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0628210 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 98 people (21.8%) under the age of 18, 16 people (3.6%) aged 18 to 24, 99 people (22.0%) aged 25 to 44, 113 people (25.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 123 people (27.4%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 48.3{{nbsp}}years.    For every 100 females, there were 96.9 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 182 housing units at an average density of {{convert|166.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 174 (95.6%) were occupied. Of these, 116 (66.7%) were owner-occupied, and 58 (33.3%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

